ation, Park Forest Middle School AYP Overview, September 29, 2011</ref> According to a report by the Pennsylvania Department of Education, 100% of its teachers were rated \"Highly Qualified\" under No Child Left Behind.<ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, Professional Qualifications of Teachers Park Forest Middle School, September 29, 2011</ref>\n\n'''PSSA Results: '''\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-1-of-2}}\n'''8th Grade Reading:'''\n*2015 - 74.1 percent proficient or higher Cumulative Mount Nittany and Park Forest Middle Schools\n*2014 - not reported\n*2013 - not reported\n*2012 - 95% on grade level (2% below basic). State - 79% \n*2011 - 92% (3% below basic). State - 81.8% <ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, Park Forest Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2011, September 29, 2011</ref>\n*2010 - 93% (5% below basic). State - 81% \n*2009 - 93% (4% below basic), State - 80% \n{{col-2-of-2}}\n'''8th Grade Math:'''\n*2015 - 51 percent proficient or higher Cumulative Mount Nittany and Park Forest Middle Schools\n*2014 - not reported\n*2013 - note reported\n*2012 - 93% on grade level (3% below basic). State - 76% <ref>{{cite web |url=http://paayp.emetric.net/Content/reportcards/RC12S110148002000006234.PDF |title=Park Forest Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2012 |author=Pennsylvania Department of Education |date=September 21, 2012}}</ref>\n*2011 - 90% (4% below basic). State - 76.9% \n*2010 - 94% (2% below basic). State - 75% <ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, 2010 PSSAs: Reading, Math, Writing Results, September 14, 2010</ref>\n*2009 - 82% (8% below basic). State - 71% <ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, 2009 PSSAs: Reading, Math, Writing and Science Results, October 20, 2009</ref>\n{{col-end}}\n\n'''8th Grade Science:'''\n*2015 - not reported\n*2014 - not reported\n*2013 - not reported\n*2012 - 82% on grade level (7% below basic). State - 59% \n*2011 - 74% (13% below basic). State \u2013 58.3% \n*2010 - 85% (6% below basic). 